## 13. Conclusions and Practical Recommendations
I built a leakage-safe, end-to-end pipeline — data-quality checks, train-only preprocessing with target encoding, 15 engineered features, 60-combo sklearn and 55-combo H2O GLM tuning by AUCPR, F1-threshold optimization, and a locked Test evaluation. The strongest signals were loan structure (SBA guarantee share, bank exposure), lender history (target-encoded bank/geography), and industry sector. Final performance is summarized in Section 9 (‹run›). I recommend using the model as a risk-flagging aid alongside human review rather than an automatic decision, and improving it with non-linear models (e.g. gradient boosting) for comparison and with time-based validation. Key risks are the class imbalance, drift in bank/economic conditions over time, and target-encoding leakage if not refit carefully on Train only.
